<dl id="n36187a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36187a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36187a"> 187(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> galligaskins</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Certain elegant and ingenious writers on the subject declare in favour of <i>Tin</i> or rather <i>Thin</i> Breeches; whence they infer that the original bearer of it was a poor but a merry rogue, whose <mark>galligaskins</mark> were none of the soundest. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 30</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
